Lake Koshkonong was sampled on 7/16/2008 by Michael Sorge and Cami Peterson.  Water levels on the lake are or were still 2-3 feet higher than normal due to the rainfall in June and July.  Air temp was 79degree F- winds were 5-7mph WSW.  Cloud cover was 80%- humidity was high.  Water was clear with some blue green algae present.  Secchi Depth was 1.5 feet.

column1: Water level is still slightly high for this time of year.  Water is green and murky- with some filamentous algae.

column2: extremely high winds and large waves made it very difficult to get an accurate temp/DO profile reading. We were only able to get a 1m integrated sample for phosphorus and chlorophyll due to shallow depth and large waves.
